FT  23 SEP 93 / People: Bodies politic
Helen Maslen, personnel director of Guy's and St Thomas' Hospital Trust, has
been appointed the first civilian director of personnel for the METROPOLITAN
POLICE. A former RAF officer, Maslen, 47, is a former personnel manager of
the Trent Health Authority and of Oxford Regional Health Authority, where
she introduced individual performance review and performance-related pay for
senior managers. As director of personnel at Northamptonshire County
Council, she devolved personnel functions to individual units and introduced
a reward strategy for senior and middle managers. At the Met she will have
responsibility for 46,000 employees - both police and civilian - and will be
a member of the Yard's policy committee. She will be on a three-year
contract and takes office on January 1.
